parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling at low RPM can cause the motorcycle to lose power and stall, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially when crossing intersections or navigating heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls when accelerating from a stop
slowing down

or coming to a stop; the engine stumbles and sometimes completely stalls; the motorcycle stalls randomly at low speeds; the engine dies under load under 5000 RPM if the clutch is not quickly pulled in; RPMS rise without throttle to 3500 RPM even when warm and trying to slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fueling issue at low RPM can cause the engine to stall, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially when crossing intersections or navigating heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls at low RPM
especially when accelerating from a stop or slowing down; the engine stumbles and sometimes completely stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ECU software issue can cause the engine to stall, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially when crossing intersections or navigating heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls randomly at low speeds; the engine dies under load under 5000 RPM if the clutch is not quickly pulled in; RPMS rise without throttle to 3500 RPM even when warm and trying to slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause accidents, near-misses, or leave the rider stranded, especially when it occurs at low speeds, such as when entering an intersection or accelerating from a stop.
symptoms: The engine stalls unexpectedly
often at low RPM
when releasing the clutch lever
or during acceleration or deceleration. The stalling can occur at any time
including when the vehicle is moving
stopped
or accelerating away from an intersection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty ECU programming can cause the engine to stall unexpectedly, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially in heavy traffic situations.
symptoms: The engine stalls randomly
often at low speeds
when entering an intersection
or during slow maneuvers in heavy traffic. The stalling can occur without warning
and the vehicle may suddenly lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The air box failure can cause catastrophic engine failure, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The air box filter allows dirt and sand to bypass and enter the engine directly
which can cause engine damage over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected stalling of the engine at low speeds or when slowing down can cause the motorcycle to lose power and control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the motorcycle loses power and control
the engine shuts off at low RPM or low vehicle speed
the motorcycle is prone to stalling when slowing down or coasting
the engine has a high idle
and fueling is poor throughout the rev range.
